“Pyros: written on Fire”
Yesterday i enjoyed these handmade canvases & artworks that also represents the first solo exposition of my friend @patrickeduardo .
That’s a wonderful composition of calligraphy made in acrylic canvases.
He’s absolutely killing it and i wish him all the best.
You can enjoy them till November 16 at @kougalleryrome

“Enjoying this huge natural reserve which surrounds the canyon where we can find the river Cassibile.
This beautiful place is located near Avola, in the southern part of Syracuse, where you can do an escursion in a 1,7km pathway (not really easy and absolutely not suggested for childs, honestly) to enjoy beautiful panoramic views, a full-immersion in the nature and finally reach “Laghetti di Cavagrande” (Cavagrande Lakes).
The incredibile scenery it’s absolutely worth the effort and i assure you’ll not be disappointed.”
